            "id": 6020021,
            "title": "研調：全球手機2025年產量恐減1% 印度生產市占首破20%創新高",
            "description": "<main class=\"c1tt5pk2\" id=\"article-container\" style=\"--c1tt5pk2-0:20px\"><section style=\"margin-top:30px\"><p>研調機構 Counterpoint Research 發布最新報告指出，2025 年全球智慧型手機製造產量預計將年減 1%，主要受關稅政策影響及整體產業需求趨緩所致，此趨勢與 2024 年 4% 年成長率形成對比，反映製造市場面臨新挑戰。</p></section><p></p><div class=\"c1hvmcli\"><figure><div class=\"iirgi4a\"><img alt=\"cover image of news article\" class=\"cr8g41v\" data-nimg=\"fill\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" sizes=\"\n            (max-width: 1024px) 100% 406px,\n            (max-width: 768px) 100% 193px\n          \" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75\" srcset=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=16&amp;q=75 16w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=32&amp;q=75 32w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=48&amp;q=75 48w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=64&amp;q=75 64w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=96&amp;q=75 96w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=128&amp;q=75 128w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=256&amp;q=75 256w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=384&amp;q=75 384w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=640&amp;q=75 640w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 750w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=828&amp;q=75 828w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1080w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=1200&amp;q=75 1200w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 1920w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=2048&amp;q=75 2048w, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcimg.cnyes.cool%2Fprod%2Fnews%2F6020021%2Fl%2F096fff58ebfd2857312a059632f1ffeb.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75 3840w\" style=\"position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent\"/></div><figcaption class=\"c1gcnfq1\">研調：全球手機2025年產量恐減1% 印度生產市占首破20%創新高。(圖：shutterstock)</figcaption></figure></div><section style=\"margin-top:30px\">\n</section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\"><p>中國預期將受關稅衝擊最為明顯，製造產量將出現下滑，加上中國國內市場表現不振，對整體製造規模造成壓力。相對而言，印度有望成為最大受益者，製造產量將以雙位數百分比成長，占比首次突破全球總量 20%。</p></section><section>\n</section><!--$--><!--/$--><section style=\"margin-top:30px\"><p>Counterpoint 資深分析師 Ivan Lam 表示，疫情後手機品牌商積極重新調整全球製造布局，關稅政策推動更加速產線外移趨勢。印度與越南因具備相對優勢，成為產能擴展與布局轉移的主要受惠市場。</p></section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\">\n</section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\"><p>印度成長主要來自 Apple 與 Samsung 等品牌增加出口導向生產，經過近十年發展與投資，印度本地電子製造能力顯著提升。政府近期推動電子零組件製造獎勵計畫，期望進一步強化在地供應鏈基礎。</p></section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\">\n</section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\"><p>越南在現有成熟供應鏈基礎上，持續吸引 Samsung 與 Motorola 等品牌加大產線配置，穩固其全球製造樞紐地位。該國作為全球製造與出口重鎮，預計也將呈現穩健成長。</p></section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\">\n</section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\"><p>Counterpoint 共同創辦人及研究副總裁 Neil Shah 指出，若手機品牌將生產轉移至美國等高成本地區，成品價格可能上漲 15% 至 20%。他強調建構完整製造生態系統需長時間累積，當前具備大規模製造能力的國家多已投入多年。</p></section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\">\n</section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\"><p>其他地區製造占比相對較低，受限於本地市場需求與投資規模，短期內預計仍將維持小幅下滑趨勢。在全球智慧型手機需求依然受限情況下，這些原本占比較低的市場預期將面臨下滑壓力。</p></section><section style=\"margin-top:30px\">\n</section></main>",
